The paper deals with communication channels and their capacity, which falls under the field of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses interference alignment, which is a technique used in network information theory (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper proposes a new communication scheme, which involves signal processing (cs.SI) and potentially machine learning (cs.MM). Finally, the paper's focus on X-channels and fully-connected networks suggests that it may also fall under the category of computer engineering (cs.CE).
